=\r\nnny intuition. They may sometimes seem to &quot;read your mind&quot; and address what=\r\n you are thinking, without you saying anything. Some of you may even develo=\r\np such an ability in future. Even if intuition is not good in general, it m=\r\nay become very good with certain people or certain matters.\n=A0\nI want to s=\r\nay a few words about such phenomena and say a few words of caution.\n=A0\n*=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nSome people are more &quot;aw=\r\nare&quot; in their intuition, while some people are not so aware and simply reso=\r\nnate to others&#39; thoughts without awareness.\n=A0\nAs an example, someone I kn=\r\now does homam everyday and is a regular and rational person without an imag=\r\ninative/intuitive mind that gets visions, dreams etc.\n=A0\nThough his sadhan=\r\na was saattwik (even his visualization of fierce deities was in Upanishadic=\r\n terms), oneday he felt a strong urge to mix blood in rice and offer it in =\r\nhomam. It did not seem natural to him and so he did not act on that instinc=\r\nt though it re-appeared in his mind several times that day. He ignored it a=\r\ns an unnatural thought for him.\n=A0\nA couple of days later, he received a m=\r\nail from someone close to him but living 1000s of miles away. This person h=\r\nappened to go to a smashan that weekend night for meditation and saw some T=\r\nantriks doing a\n &quot;Rakta Chamunda&quot; homam. They were offering ingredients dip=\r\nped in their blood in homam. He just sat there and observed them. He later =\r\nsent a mail about it.\n=A0\nWhen the original person received the mail, he re=\r\nalized why he had that thought a couple of days back. His mind was simply r=\r\nesonating to the thoughts of the other person, without a complete awareness=\r\n. In fact, such a thing happened to him several times with the same person.=\r\n\n=A0\nThere were also many occasions when he would randomly talk about some =\r\ntopic and one specific person in the room would claim that that person was =\r\nthinking about exactly that topic. Again, the question in the mind of that =\r\nperson resonated in the other mind and the person started talking about it.=\r\n\n\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nFirst, how does t=\r\nhis work? Simple - resonance between minds.\n=A0\nSuppose you are talking lou=\r\nd. You may not hear what others around you are saying. Similarly, if your m=\r\nind is vibrating with too many thoughts, it may not resonate to the vibrati=\r\nons in other minds around it.\n=A0\nBut, if you are relatively calm, you can =\r\nhear what others are saying. Similarly, if your mind is relatively calm, it=\r\n may pick up vibrations in other minds around it (or even 1000s of miles aw=\r\nay if there is some attachment/connection) and resonate to those vibrations=\r\n!\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nSecond, how to kn=\r\now where the thought is coming from?\n=A0\nWhen an infant listens to tens of =\r\nvoices, he simply hears different sounds and does not know from which face =\r\neach sound is coming from. Over time, after many observations and correlati=\r\nons, brain learns to discern from which face each sound is coming from. Lat=\r\ner, one may recognize a voice even when the face is behind a curtain or oth=\r\nerwise invisible!\n=A0\nSimilarly, if one so wishes, one can develop the abil=\r\nity to discern the source of each thought that vibrates the mind, after muc=\r\nh observation and correlation. The mind can of course be trained. However, =\r\na seeker of self-realization need not actively pursue such an ability, for =\r\nit serves no useful purpose in Self-realization.\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nThe ability to \ncalm the vibrations in the mi=\r\nnd due to conditioning and then the ability to calm any vibrations due to r=\r\nesonance is more important than the \nability to discern the source of vibra=\r\ntions.\n=A0\nWhether a thought that vibrates one&#39;s mind right now is coming f=\r\nrom one&#39;s own conditioning or sensory observation or someone else&#39;s, is not=\r\n the crux. The crux is knowing whether one should perform any physical/ment=\r\nal *action* based on thought, to fulfill one&#39;s swa-dharma, or just observe =\r\nthe thought and leave it (move on). A true seeker&#39;s focus will be on that a=\r\nbility, i.e. developing clarity regarding one&#39;s own dharma, than figuring o=\r\nut the source of each thought. The latter can be a distraction or even an e=\r\ngo trap.\n=A0\nNevertheless, Nature may sometimes give one abilities that one=\r\n does not actively pursue or need (perhaps because one desired it long back=\r\n). A true seeker neither tries for nor resists what is not needed by one. O=\r\nne does not dwell on it in either case and moves on.\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nOne may argue that certain special abil=\r\nities can help one pay off karmik debts on one&#39;s way to liberation. However=\r\n, one can (must) trust Nature to arrange for circumstances to pay off one&#39;s=\r\n debts. The key is to be aware of what one can give others in any given cir=\r\ncumstance and give it without holding back. If one gets used to giving with=\r\nout expecting any payback, Nature will automatically arrange for all of one=\r\n&#39;s debts to be paid off. No special abilities are needed.\n=A0\nOf course, wh=\r\nen there is a clash between giving thing X to person A vs giving thing Y to=\r\n person B, one needs to use one&#39;s discretion. That is where our conditionin=\r\ng may block us from the right call. As we know our dharma better and get a =\r\nsense of which of our dharmas are higher, we may start to make the right ca=\r\nlls.\n=A0\nThe bottomline: Try to know your dharma (declared by the spark of =\r\ndivinity in heart). Try to follow it to the best of ability. Give whatever =\r\nyou can give others, without expecting any payback. Ignore thoughts arising=\r\n in mind, which do not contribute to fulfillment of your dharma, no matter =\r\nwhat the source of that thought may be.\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nBefore I sign off, a couple of words on Rakta Chamund=\r\na from the story above.\n=A0\nThe verb cham means to \ndrink/eat/consume. The =\r\nverb mund means to shave or deplete. Chamunda \nmeans one who drinks and fin=\r\nishes. Rakta means conditioning or coloring \n(the words rakti (attachment) =\r\nand virakti (detachment) come from the \nsame root). Rakta Chamunda is the o=\r\nne who drinks and empties all \nconditioning that causes desires. Offering b=\r\nlood is an approximation. Also, ironic that some people worship Rakta Chamu=\r\nnda for vashikaran..\n=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spiri=\r\ntuality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\r\n---1999499579-139601118-1375066402=:21945\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#000; background-color:#fff; font-family:ar=\r\nial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;=\r\ndiv style=3D&quot;color:#000;background-color:#fff;font-family:arial, helvetica,=\r\n sans-serif;font-size:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv259588=\r\n4606yui_3_7_2_3201_1373624150759_66&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_3201=\r\n_1373624150759_67&quot; class=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_3201_1373624150759_55&quot; s=\r\ntyle=3D&quot;color:#000;background-color:#fff;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans=\r\n-serif;font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606y=\r\nui_3_7_2_2741_1373624150759_65&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2741_1373=\r\n624150759_66&quot; class=3D&quot;yiv25