;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595=\r\n884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2=\r\n026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;The ability to \ncalm the vibrations in the mind due t=\r\no conditioning and then the ability\n to calm any vibrations due to resonanc=\r\ne is more important than the \nability to discern the source of vibrations.&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_6=\r\n8&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Whether a thought that vibrates one&#39;s mind right now is coming fr=\r\nom one&#39;s own conditioning or sensory observation or someone else&#39;s, is not =\r\nthe crux. The crux is knowing whether one should perform any physical/menta=\r\nl *action* based on thought, to fulfill one&#39;s swa-dharma, or just observe t=\r\nhe thought and leave it (move on). A true seeker&#39;s focus will be on that ab=\r\nility, i.e. developing clarity regarding one&#39;s own dharma, than figuring ou=\r\nt the source of each thought. The latter can be a distraction or even an eg=\r\no trap.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Nevertheless, Nature may sometimes give one abilities =\r\nthat one does not actively pursue or need (perhaps because one desired it l=\r\nong back). A true seeker neither tries for nor resists what is not needed b=\r\ny one. One does not dwell on it in either case and moves on.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\n/span&gt;&lt;span\n id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;s=\r\npan id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_137=\r\n3624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;On=\r\ne may argue that certain &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_137=\r\n3624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;sp=\r\necial &lt;/span&gt;abilities can help one pay off karmik debts on one&#39;s way to li=\r\nberation. However, one can (must) trust Nature to arrange for circumstances=\r\n to pay off one&#39;s debts. The key is to be aware of what one can give others=\r\n in any given circumstance and give it without holding back. If one gets us=\r\ned to giving without expecting any payback, Nature will automatically arran=\r\nge for all of one&#39;s debts to be paid off. No special abilities are needed.&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Of course, when there is a clash between giving thing X to per=\r\nson A vs giving\n thing Y to person B, one needs to use one&#39;s discretion. Th=\r\nat is where our conditioning may block us from the right call. As we know o=\r\nur dharma better and get a sense of which of our dharmas are higher, we may=\r\n start to make the right calls.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;The bottomline: Try to know yo=\r\nur dharma (declared by the spark of divinity in heart). Try to follow it to=\r\n the best of ability. Give whatever you can give others, without expecting =\r\nany payback. Ignore thoughts arising in mind, which do not contribute to fu=\r\nlfillment of your dharma, no matter what the source of that thought may be.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_=\r\n68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span=\r\n id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_137362=\r\n4150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Befor=\r\ne I sign off, a\n couple of words on Rakta Chamunda from the story above.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150=\r\n759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;The=\r\n verb cham means to \ndrink/eat/consume. The verb mund means to shave or dep=\r\nlete. Chamunda \nmeans one who drinks and finishes. Rakta means conditioning=\r\n or coloring \n(the words rakti (attachment) and virakti (detachment) come f=\r\nrom the \nsame root). Rakta Chamunda is the one who drinks and empties all \n=\r\nconditioning that causes desires. Offering blood is an approximation. Also,=\r\n ironic that some people worship Rakta Chamunda for vashikaran..&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\n/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology=\r\n &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/di=\r\nv&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_60 yiv2595884606y=\r\nui_3_7_2_2554_1373624150759_59 yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_2741_1373624150759_60=\r\n\n yiv2595884606yui_3_7_2_3201_1373624150759_61&quot; id=3D&quot;yiv2595884606yui_3_7_=\r\n2_2026_1373624150759_61&quot; style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;font-fa=\r\nmily:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-=\r\nstyle:normal;&quot;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/=\r\ndiv&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\r\n---1999499579-139601118-1375066402=:21945--\r\n\n"}}